      • setCustomer

        public SessionCreateParams.Builder setCustomer(java.lang.String customer)
        ID of an existing customer, if one exists. The email stored on the customer will be used to prefill the email field on the Checkout page. If the customer changes their email on the Checkout page, the Customer object will be updated with the new email. If blank for Checkout Sessions in payment or subscription mode, Checkout will create a new customer object based on information provided during the session.

      • setCustomerEmail

        public SessionCreateParams.Builder setCustomerEmail(java.lang.String customerEmail)
        If provided, this value will be used when the Customer object is created. If not provided, customers will be asked to enter their email address. Use this parameter to prefill customer data if you already have an email on file. To access information about the customer once a session is complete, use the customer field.
